{
  "description": "The package is designed to automate the simulation of solitaire games and implement various playing strategies for testing and evaluation purposes.",
  "layer": "Service Layer",
  "layerReason": "This package fits the Service Layer because it orchestrates the simulation of solitaire games and connects the gameplay logic with performance metrics, acting as a coordinator between the domain logic and the overall application flow. It does not fit the Presentation Layer as it does not manage user interface elements or user interactions. Additionally, it is not part of the Domain Layer since it primarily focuses on service provision and automation rather than encapsulating business logic or domain data representation."
}

{
  "description": "The purpose of the package is to provide a structured representation and management of playing cards and their associated functionalities for a solitaire game.",
  "layer": "Domain Layer",
  "layerReason": "This package fits the Domain Layer as it encapsulates the business logic related to card games, including the representation of cards, their ranks and suits, and the management of card collections such as decks and stacks. The classes and enums serve as information holders and service providers that define the core data and behaviors necessary for gameplay. It does not fit the Presentation Layer, as there are no UI elements or user interface management present. Additionally, it does not belong to the Service Layer, as it does not orchestrate application flow or connect UI events with domain logic, but rather focuses on the domain data and operations themselves."
}

{
  "description": "The purpose of the package is to provide the graphical user interface components and functionalities for a Solitaire game application, enabling user interactions with various game elements.",
  "layer": "Presentation Layer",
  "layerReason": "This package fits the Presentation Layer because it contains classes that manage the user interface and user interactions, such as card dragging and visual representation of game elements. The classes are primarily focused on displaying information and responding to user input, which aligns with the responsibilities of the Presentation Layer. The other layers, such as the Service Layer and Domain Layer, are not applicable here as they deal with application flow and business logic, respectively, which are not the focus of this package."
}

{
  "description": "This package encapsulates the core logic and data structures necessary for managing a solitaire game, including moves, game state, and the organization of card piles.",
  "layer": "Domain Layer",
  "layerReason": "The package primarily focuses on the business logic and data representation of the solitaire game, which is characteristic of the domain layer. It contains classes and interfaces that define the rules, state management, and operations related to the game, such as moves and card management. It does not manage user interface elements or application flow, which are responsibilities of the presentation and service layers, respectively."
}
